cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development of a monitoring and control system for a public cluster. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the system includes web-based user interfaces for daily operation. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of the system using microcontrollers and dedicated software. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the development of an autonomous control system based on real-time monitoring. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of a dedicated microcontroller for the system implementation.
